1
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,466
[♪]

2
00:01:04,548 --> 00:01:06,927
KISAGARI:
Bright lights, big city,
old story.

3
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:09,760
Hatchling, fresh off the farm,
wants to spread her wings.

4
00:01:09,794 --> 00:01:11,927
Drawn to Metro
like a duck to water.

5
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:13,294
Folks at home worried sick.

6
00:01:13,327 --> 00:01:15,660
That's where I come in.

7
00:01:15,694 --> 00:01:18,127
Name's Kisagari.
I'm a detective.

8
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,294
Hmm?

9
00:01:19,327 --> 00:01:22,960
There, that's a ducky.

10
00:01:27,927 --> 00:01:29,860
Another dead end.

11
00:01:29,894 --> 00:01:32,660
Hmm.

12
00:01:32,694 --> 00:01:34,894
The old MetroWorld
Amusement Park.

13
00:01:34,927 --> 00:01:37,227
Shuttered up years ago.

14
00:01:37,260 --> 00:01:40,860
Just a wild goose chase.

15
00:01:40,894 --> 00:01:44,727
I'll find you yet.

16
00:01:46,694 --> 00:01:49,027
You're a wily bird,
I'll give you that.

17
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:52,760
But now you're matching wits
against Kisag-g-g--

18
00:01:52,794 --> 00:01:53,760
[SNEEZES]

19
00:01:55,927 --> 00:01:58,294
Gotta get out of
this night air and into--

20
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:00,294
MAN: ...hot water with
the old lady.

21
00:02:00,327 --> 00:02:02,694
MAN 2: Why is she
so mad at Norton?

22
00:02:02,727 --> 00:02:04,094
He quit his job.

23
00:02:04,127 --> 00:02:06,994
Swears he was attacked
down in the sewer by a ghost.

24
00:02:07,027 --> 00:02:09,660
And he's not
the only one.

25
00:02:09,694 --> 00:02:12,860
I heard it's been haunting
all the tunnels around here.

26
00:02:12,894 --> 00:02:14,860
They also say,
first you hear a sound

27
00:02:14,894 --> 00:02:17,360
like the rustling
of wings.

28
00:02:17,394 --> 00:02:19,608
Yeah, the only sound
Norton heard

29
00:02:19,641 --> 00:02:21,341
was the cuckoo clock
ringing in his head.

30
00:02:21,374 --> 00:02:22,574
Cuckoo! Cuckoo! Cuckoo!

31
00:02:22,608 --> 00:02:23,641
[RUSTLING]

32
00:02:23,674 --> 00:02:25,174
BOTH:
Huh?

33
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,674
You hear something?

34
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:29,741
Like rustling wings?

35
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:32,408
[EERIE MOANING]

36
00:02:37,541 --> 00:02:40,241
[ROARING]

37
00:02:40,274 --> 00:02:41,574
[BOTH SCREAMING]

38
00:02:41,608 --> 00:02:43,041
That ain't
no cuckoo bird!

39
00:02:52,074 --> 00:02:53,541
ALEJO:
Did you see the news?

40
00:02:53,574 --> 00:02:57,274
More workers were attacked
in the tunnels last night.

41
00:02:57,308 --> 00:02:59,108
Ghost isn't just angry,
it's hungry.

42
00:02:59,141 --> 00:03:00,741
If it finds you, you're lunch!

43
00:03:00,774 --> 00:03:02,674
Not me.
I'm too bony.

44
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:04,374
Chill out,
you guys.

45
00:03:04,408 --> 00:03:07,308
I bet Astro could knock
that ghost out with one punch.

46
00:03:07,341 --> 00:03:10,074
So how about
it, Astro?

47
00:03:10,108 --> 00:03:12,708
Up for a little extracurricular
ghost-busting this afternoon?

48
00:03:12,741 --> 00:03:14,108
That sounds great.

49
00:03:14,141 --> 00:03:16,774
All right!
You in, Abercrombie?

50
00:03:16,808 --> 00:03:19,408
Sure. I'll watch
Astro's back.

51
00:03:19,441 --> 00:03:21,274
But I can't.
ALL: Huh?

52
00:03:21,308 --> 00:03:23,674
It's just that Dr. O'Shay has

53
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:26,274
a superimportant mission
for me to do today.

54
00:03:26,308 --> 00:03:27,374
ALL:
Ohh!

55
00:03:27,408 --> 00:03:29,408
No problem.

56
00:03:29,441 --> 00:03:31,241
We can even go
without my brother.

57
00:03:31,274 --> 00:03:33,041
Huh?

58
00:03:33,074 --> 00:03:35,574
Too bad. Astro could've
shown that ghost who's boss.

59
00:03:35,608 --> 00:03:36,608
Maybe another day.

60
00:03:38,274 --> 00:03:39,774
ZORAN:
Hold it!

61
00:03:39,808 --> 00:03:41,674
I said I'd bust
the ghost with you.

62
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:43,541
We'd have no chance without
Astro.

63
00:03:43,574 --> 00:03:45,108
Yeah. We're not
superheroes, Zoran.

64
00:03:48,474 --> 00:03:49,441
I am.

65
00:03:49,474 --> 00:03:51,208
Upgrades?

66
00:03:51,241 --> 00:03:54,608
ZORAN: So I can be
like my brother.

67
00:03:54,641 --> 00:03:56,708
A whole new Zoran.

68
00:03:56,741 --> 00:04:01,041
I wanna fly and breath fire and
be twice as strong as Astro.

69
00:04:02,608 --> 00:04:05,208
Breathe fire?
Hmm.

70
00:04:05,241 --> 00:04:08,041
All heroes need
cool signature moves.

71
00:04:10,341 --> 00:04:13,774
So, Zoran, why all this sudden
desire for more powers?

72
00:04:13,808 --> 00:04:16,074
It's not fair!

73
00:04:16,108 --> 00:04:17,774
Why should my brother
be the only one

74
00:04:17,808 --> 00:04:19,741
who gets to save the day
all the time?

75
00:04:19,774 --> 00:04:22,141
But you have to understand,

76
00:04:22,174 --> 00:04:24,374
you're truly wonderful
in so many other ways.

77
00:04:24,408 --> 00:04:25,641
ASTRO: Doctor.
Huh?

78
00:04:25,674 --> 00:04:28,074
I drained the radiation
from the power modules

79
00:04:28,108 --> 00:04:29,774
I removed from
the downed robots.

80
00:04:29,808 --> 00:04:32,474
And in the nick of time.
Nice work, Astro.

81
00:04:32,508 --> 00:04:33,608
Mmm!

82
00:04:33,641 --> 00:04:34,641
Huh?

83
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:36,674
Astro! Astro! Astro!

84
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:38,374
Hmm!

85
00:04:38,408 --> 00:04:39,574
Hey!

86
00:04:39,608 --> 00:04:41,441
What's eating
Zoran?

87
00:04:41,474 --> 00:04:43,141
Astro,
it will pass.

88
00:04:43,174 --> 00:04:44,441
How soon?

89
00:04:44,474 --> 00:04:45,474
[SQUAWKS]

90
00:04:45,508 --> 00:04:47,808
Momo!

91
00:04:47,841 --> 00:04:51,441
Doctor, trouble. Another
six robots have gone down.

92
00:04:51,474 --> 00:04:53,408
This is really getting
out of hand.

93
00:04:53,441 --> 00:04:56,141
Yuko, can you pull up the video?
We should see this.

94
00:04:56,174 --> 00:04:59,174
YUKO: On it.
ASTRO: It's like an epidemic!

95
00:05:00,808 --> 00:05:02,641
We have to
find the cause!

96
00:05:02,674 --> 00:05:05,141
I'll show them
who's tough!

97
00:05:05,174 --> 00:05:10,174
When I take down that ghost,
they'll beg to hang with me.

98
00:05:12,441 --> 00:05:17,674
Now, if I were a ghost,
where would I cry "boo"?

99
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:20,108
Where I'd get a good echo!

100
00:05:28,241 --> 00:05:29,241
[SQUEAKING]

101
00:05:29,274 --> 00:05:30,341
[YELLS]

102
00:05:30,374 --> 00:05:32,241
[PANTING]

103
00:05:32,274 --> 00:05:34,374
It's safe to come out now,
Mr. Ghost.

104
00:05:34,408 --> 00:05:36,574
I've scared away the rats!

105
00:05:36,608 --> 00:05:39,708
Oh, every robot knows
there's no such thing as ghosts.

106
00:05:39,741 --> 00:05:41,208
Who am I kidding?

107
00:05:41,241 --> 00:05:42,241
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

108
00:05:42,274 --> 00:05:43,508
Huh?

109
00:05:43,541 --> 00:05:46,041
A ghost! Ahh!

110
00:05:46,074 --> 00:05:47,574
[YELLS]

111
00:05:49,408 --> 00:05:51,274
KISAGARI: I just had
this suit dry-cleaned.

112
00:05:51,308 --> 00:05:54,608
And I think I broke
my tailbone.

113
00:05:54,641 --> 00:05:57,041
Then you're really
not a ghost?

114
00:05:57,074 --> 00:05:59,174
Almost, thanks to you.

115
00:06:01,508 --> 00:06:03,341
O'SHAY:
People are getting worried.

116
00:06:03,374 --> 00:06:05,374
Soon we'll have a real panic
on our hands.

117
00:06:05,408 --> 00:06:07,408
Yes, but the good news
is Momo's found

118
00:06:07,441 --> 00:06:10,174
what's been causing
all the robot shutdowns.

119
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:12,641
Look.

120
00:06:12,674 --> 00:06:16,474
Oh, no, it's
detecting IS-13!

121
00:06:16,508 --> 00:06:20,474
Yuko, IS-13
comes from Dexanol-G,

122
00:06:20,508 --> 00:06:24,041
that toxic chemical used in
old robot energy modules, right?

123
00:06:24,074 --> 00:06:27,574
Ah-huh, and it's
the same type of poison

124
00:06:27,608 --> 00:06:29,774
<i>that those horrible Repo Girls</i>
<i>released into Dragon Lake</i>

125
00:06:29,808 --> 00:06:32,241
<i>when they were</i>
<i>illegally dumping there.</i>

126
00:06:32,274 --> 00:06:35,474
<i>That is, until you</i>
<i>stopped them, Astro.</i>

127
00:06:35,508 --> 00:06:37,341
Hmm.

128
00:06:37,374 --> 00:06:39,374
So obviously,
somewhere around here

129
00:06:39,408 --> 00:06:42,274
something has been
leaking toxic waste.

130
00:06:42,308 --> 00:06:43,708
Hmm. Wait!

131
00:06:46,441 --> 00:06:48,608
Huh?
What's wrong, Astro?

132
00:06:48,641 --> 00:06:52,808
For a moment, the whole city
seemed to bend and warp.

133
00:06:52,841 --> 00:06:55,208
YUKO:
Astro's right.

134
00:06:55,241 --> 00:06:58,308
Space itself has become unstable
around here.

135
00:06:58,341 --> 00:07:00,508
I believe a large quantity
of toxic waste

136
00:07:00,541 --> 00:07:02,474
has been dumped
into hyperspace.

137
00:07:02,508 --> 00:07:05,674
Weakening the fabric
of space-time.

138
00:07:05,708 --> 00:07:09,208
If this gets any worse, we could
be facing a catastrophic--

139
00:07:09,241 --> 00:07:11,341
ASTRO:
Dimensional collapse!

140
00:07:11,374 --> 00:07:13,808
O'SHAY: It could
tear our world apart.

141
00:07:13,841 --> 00:07:16,041
[ALL LAUGHING]

142
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,104
KISAGARI: Oh,
you've never heard of

143
00:07:24,137 --> 00:07:26,170
Wally Kisagari,
world-famous detective?

144
00:07:26,204 --> 00:07:27,204
ZORAN:
No.

145
00:07:27,237 --> 00:07:30,237
[SNEEZES]

146
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:32,637
So why are you
looking for a duck?

147
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:34,604
Because she's missing.

148
00:07:34,637 --> 00:07:36,570
And you should know
many people recognize me

149
00:07:36,604 --> 00:07:39,570
by my handsome profile.

150
00:07:39,604 --> 00:07:43,137
Hmm. So do detectives
catch ducks to eat them?

151
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,137
Wait a minute, kid.

152
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:47,837
So you're telling me you
don't know what a detective is.

153
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:50,237
Mm-hm.

154
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:53,137
YUKO: Doctor, I've detected
a familiar energy signature

155
00:07:53,170 --> 00:07:56,004
coming from
the dimensional warp.

156
00:07:56,037 --> 00:07:58,270
The wormhole
projector.

157
00:07:58,304 --> 00:07:59,804
Hmm.

158
00:08:02,004 --> 00:08:06,570
O'SHAY: <i>For an invention with</i>
<i>so much potential to do good,</i>

159
00:08:06,604 --> 00:08:10,704
it seems someone always
finds a way to misuse it.

160
00:08:10,737 --> 00:08:13,637
We have to find
the criminals at once, Astro,

161
00:08:13,670 --> 00:08:14,670
and stop them
from transporting

162
00:08:14,704 --> 00:08:17,804
any more toxic waste
into hyperspace.

163
00:08:17,837 --> 00:08:19,637
Got it.

164
00:08:19,670 --> 00:08:22,970
King of the world!
Whoo-hoo!

165
00:08:23,004 --> 00:08:24,604
ZORAN:
Oh, I get it.

166
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:28,870
So detectives make their
living collecting trash?

167
00:08:28,904 --> 00:08:31,270
That's not trash.
Those are my files.

168
00:08:31,304 --> 00:08:33,870
A good detective knows
everything about a case.

169
00:08:33,904 --> 00:08:35,937
What's this?
Don't touch it!

170
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,904
[SCREAMING]

171
00:08:37,937 --> 00:08:40,137
[COUGHING]

172
00:08:40,170 --> 00:08:43,204
Do you have any idea how long it
took me to organize those files?

173
00:08:43,237 --> 00:08:46,104
You're like a one-robot
demolition squad.

174
00:08:46,137 --> 00:08:48,637
I'm sorry.
Hopeless!

175
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:50,304
You're right.
I am hopeless.

176
00:08:50,337 --> 00:08:53,070
I'm not like my brother
Astro at all.

177
00:08:53,104 --> 00:08:54,937
Your brother Astro?

178
00:08:54,970 --> 00:08:57,804
You mean, you're
Astro's little sister?

179
00:08:57,837 --> 00:09:00,704
Oh, everyone knows
about my brother.

180
00:09:00,737 --> 00:09:04,204
Well, I taught him everything he
knows about being a detective.

181
00:09:04,237 --> 00:09:07,170
Yes, sir, Astro's
one heck of a robot.

182
00:09:07,204 --> 00:09:08,604
[LAUGHING]

183
00:09:08,637 --> 00:09:11,004
Everyone likes Astro
better than me.

184
00:09:11,037 --> 00:09:13,637
Well, there's
certainly nothing wrong

185
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:15,604
with trying to be
like your big brother.

186
00:09:15,637 --> 00:09:17,270
He's a pretty
amazing robot.

187
00:09:17,304 --> 00:09:19,237
Why does everyone
say that?

188
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,937
"You should be
more like Astro."

189
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:23,204
Well, no one tells Astro
to be more like me.

190
00:09:23,237 --> 00:09:25,637
KISAGARI: <i>So humans and robots</i>
<i>aren't so different after all.</i>

191
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,770
<i>I'll fix this.</i>

192
00:09:27,804 --> 00:09:29,837
Why are you
just sitting there?

193
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:33,270
Detective Kisagari and Detective
Zoran have a ghost to bust.

194
00:09:33,304 --> 00:09:34,870
Really? What about your files?

195
00:09:34,904 --> 00:09:37,837
Don't worry about them.
You did me a favor.

196
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:40,670
I never could find anything
in all this junk anyhow.

197
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:44,804
ASTRO:
This is bad!

198
00:09:44,837 --> 00:09:47,037
That toxic energy
coming from the space warp

199
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:49,204
is messing up my search systems.

200
00:09:49,237 --> 00:09:51,970
I'd better tell Dr. O'Shay.

201
00:09:57,104 --> 00:09:59,070
KISAGARI: Pay attention, kid.
You're learning from the master.

202
00:09:59,104 --> 00:10:01,637
Now we'll get to the bottom
of this ghost business.

203
00:10:01,670 --> 00:10:04,104
It sure looks like the right
kind of hang-out for a ghost,

204
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:06,004
but what makes you think
it'll show up in this tunnel?

205
00:10:06,037 --> 00:10:07,570
Take a gander.

206
00:10:07,604 --> 00:10:08,637
These red dots are the tunnels

207
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:10,904
where it's been spotted.

208
00:10:10,937 --> 00:10:13,870
I did some legwork and guess
what I found at every scene,

209
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:16,037
old broken holo-projectors

210
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:20,537
That's what's behind
this whole ghost scare, you see.

211
00:10:20,734 --> 00:10:23,455
So you mean somebody's using
a hologram projector

212
00:10:23,488 --> 00:10:25,021
to make this ghost appear?

213
00:10:25,055 --> 00:10:26,688
There's an old saying, kiddo,

214
00:10:26,721 --> 00:10:30,221
crack open a mystery and
you'll find the truth inside.

215
00:10:30,255 --> 00:10:33,933
It's all a scam,
and here's the proof.

216
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:36,391
This is the only
tunnel left

217
00:10:36,425 --> 00:10:38,425
with working
holo-projectors in it.

218
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:40,364
If I'm right,
Mr. Scary-Pants

219
00:10:40,397 --> 00:10:42,435
should put in an appearance
before too long.

220
00:10:42,468 --> 00:10:45,901
Now we just wait...

221
00:10:47,683 --> 00:10:49,383
for our very
punctual ghost.

222
00:10:54,627 --> 00:10:57,507
[BOTH SCREAMING]

223
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,573
[ROARING]

224
00:11:00,945 --> 00:11:03,078
Thanks for helping me
and all, mister,

225
00:11:03,111 --> 00:11:07,711
but we busted it so we can
just go home now, right?

226
00:11:10,078 --> 00:11:12,078
It's just a holographic
projection. It can't hurt you.

227
00:11:12,111 --> 00:11:13,311
Watch.

228
00:11:13,345 --> 00:11:15,145
♪ Scaredy-ghost
Scaredy-ghost ♪

229
00:11:15,178 --> 00:11:17,245
♪ Who's the one that's
scared the most, you are ♪

230
00:11:17,278 --> 00:11:18,345
[BLOWS RASPBERRY]

231
00:11:18,378 --> 00:11:20,611
[ROARING]

232
00:11:24,678 --> 00:11:26,645
It's almost like
he really heard you.

233
00:11:26,678 --> 00:11:27,978
State-of-the-art graphics.

234
00:11:31,278 --> 00:11:32,845
Still, why take chances?

235
00:11:36,078 --> 00:11:37,078
Huh?

236
00:11:37,111 --> 00:11:39,545
Zoran, run!

237
00:11:42,111 --> 00:11:43,745
Come on, kiddo. Come on!

238
00:11:43,778 --> 00:11:46,011
We've gotta make tracks
before it eats us.

239
00:11:46,045 --> 00:11:49,311
This ghost, it's trying
to tell us something.

240
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:54,078
Yes. It's saying,
"You look tasty."

241
00:11:54,111 --> 00:11:55,811
Can't you hear it?

242
00:11:55,845 --> 00:11:59,145
It's so sad and trying
so hard to talk to me.

243
00:11:59,178 --> 00:12:01,111
It sounds sad to you?

244
00:12:02,678 --> 00:12:04,711
Sad or not,
that thing's dangerous,

245
00:12:04,745 --> 00:12:06,278
and we're getting
out of here now.

246
00:12:06,311 --> 00:12:09,245
Hey, what's wrong with you?
You're not afraid of that thing?

247
00:12:11,645 --> 00:12:13,945
Hey, hey! you got
a screw loose or something?

248
00:12:13,978 --> 00:12:17,711
Tell me, what do you want
to say to me?

249
00:12:17,745 --> 00:12:21,778
Your world is
coming apart at the seams.

250
00:12:21,811 --> 00:12:25,211
Yeah. That sounds bad.

251
00:12:31,178 --> 00:12:34,311
Doctor, the warp in space
is spreading really fast.

252
00:12:34,345 --> 00:12:36,011
Did you find anything yet?

253
00:12:36,045 --> 00:12:38,278
According to
my calculations,

254
00:12:38,311 --> 00:12:41,711
we have only one hour
till total dimensional collapse.

255
00:12:41,745 --> 00:12:43,678
You must find
the wormhole projector

256
00:12:43,711 --> 00:12:46,111
and reverse the effects
of the damage before then.

257
00:12:46,145 --> 00:12:49,111
Right. Let's rocket!

258
00:12:50,711 --> 00:12:51,711
Stop them.

259
00:12:51,745 --> 00:12:53,645
They must not dump
any more

260
00:12:53,678 --> 00:12:56,078
dangerous materials
into hyperspace.

261
00:12:56,111 --> 00:12:58,211
Tell us, where do
we need to go?

262
00:12:58,245 --> 00:13:00,678
Here.

263
00:13:03,611 --> 00:13:06,245
Hmm? That's
the old amusement park.

264
00:13:07,878 --> 00:13:10,711
[BOTH SCREAMING]

265
00:13:13,045 --> 00:13:15,811
KISAGARI: Well, we're here.
Now what?

266
00:13:15,845 --> 00:13:19,078
The ghost said the world
was about to fall apart.

267
00:13:19,111 --> 00:13:22,211
There's some sort of awful
secret hidden around here.

268
00:13:22,245 --> 00:13:23,245
Huh?
Huh?

269
00:13:23,278 --> 00:13:25,078
ZORAN:
After that ghost,

270
00:13:25,111 --> 00:13:27,978
a haunted house
isn't spooky at all.

271
00:13:28,011 --> 00:13:29,911
I've seen
that light before.

272
00:13:29,945 --> 00:13:31,645
I think it's
coming from in here.

273
00:13:34,878 --> 00:13:37,045
KISAGARI:
Aha!

274
00:13:37,078 --> 00:13:40,911
This light is leaking out
from something down below.

275
00:13:42,211 --> 00:13:44,245
So we're
going down too.

276
00:13:44,278 --> 00:13:45,245
But how?

277
00:13:47,278 --> 00:13:48,678
Follow me.

278
00:13:55,378 --> 00:13:57,611
[BOTH SCREAMING}

279
00:13:59,278 --> 00:14:00,745
Huh?

280
00:14:00,778 --> 00:14:01,345
Oh.

281
00:14:02,911 --> 00:14:05,345
Oh, okay,
that was scary.

282
00:14:05,378 --> 00:14:07,145
Anyway, let's find a way down.

283
00:14:08,978 --> 00:14:10,878
Hold on!

284
00:14:14,945 --> 00:14:17,578
Well, I guess it's faster
than the stairs.

285
00:14:17,611 --> 00:14:18,678
ZORAN: What is
this place?

286
00:14:18,711 --> 00:14:20,578
KISAGARI: It reminds me
of a dream I had

287
00:14:20,611 --> 00:14:22,345
after eating
too many sloppy joes.

288
00:14:22,378 --> 00:14:24,811
ZORAN: You sure have
weird dreams.

289
00:14:24,845 --> 00:14:27,111
Kid, you don't know
the half of it.

290
00:14:27,145 --> 00:14:30,911
Do you feel that? It's like some
kind of really weird energy.

291
00:14:30,945 --> 00:14:34,311
I think it may be
toxic industrial waste.

292
00:14:34,345 --> 00:14:36,745
Why is it
all here?

293
00:14:38,345 --> 00:14:40,863
SARA: Because this
is where we work.

294
00:14:40,896 --> 00:14:42,096
Who's there?

295
00:14:42,129 --> 00:14:43,963
[REPO GIRLS LAUGHING]

296
00:14:43,996 --> 00:14:48,396
Three simple businesswomen
out to make an honest buck.

297
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,463
ALL:
The Repo Girls.

298
00:14:50,496 --> 00:14:53,963
You know, it's rude to
drop in on people unannounced.

299
00:14:53,996 --> 00:14:57,463
As you see, we're really not
set up to entertain company.

300
00:14:57,496 --> 00:14:59,996
Just what kind
of sleazy racket

301
00:15:00,029 --> 00:15:01,729
are you ladies
running here anyway?

302
00:15:01,763 --> 00:15:05,396
Sorry, but we have to
get back to work.

303
00:15:06,996 --> 00:15:08,496
King Nagha can keep you company.

304
00:15:08,529 --> 00:15:09,996
Ahh!
No thanks!

305
00:15:10,029 --> 00:15:11,796
But he's
very talented.

306
00:15:11,829 --> 00:15:15,396
King Nagha, show our guests
what you can do!

307
00:15:19,829 --> 00:15:21,829
[BOTH SCREAMING]

308
00:15:35,196 --> 00:15:37,396
[BOTH SCREAMING]

309
00:15:41,996 --> 00:15:44,863
I just detected the wormhole
projector being activated.

310
00:15:47,129 --> 00:15:49,829
No good,
I can't get an exact fix

311
00:15:49,863 --> 00:15:51,796
because of the effects
of the dimensional warping.

312
00:15:54,163 --> 00:15:55,963
Where's it sending
this stuff, huh?

313
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:57,729
Hyperspace.

314
00:15:57,763 --> 00:15:59,029
There's no limit
to the amount

315
00:15:59,063 --> 00:16:01,063
of dangerous waste
we can dispose of.

316
00:16:01,096 --> 00:16:02,596
No fuss,
no muss.

317
00:16:02,629 --> 00:16:05,629
If you keep this up,
the world's gonna fall apart.

318
00:16:05,663 --> 00:16:07,496
This is what the ghost
warned us about.

319
00:16:07,529 --> 00:16:09,996
Ghost? Oh, you met our friend.

320
00:16:10,029 --> 00:16:12,096
You're behind that too?
I'm not surprised.

321
00:16:12,129 --> 00:16:14,563
When we first activated
the projector,

322
00:16:14,596 --> 00:16:17,696
we transported a robot which
hadn't completely shut down,

323
00:16:17,729 --> 00:16:22,129
along with an unlucky duckling
that happened to fly in here.

324
00:16:22,163 --> 00:16:24,563
Did you say duckling?

325
00:16:30,096 --> 00:16:32,729
CHRIS:
It seems that during transport,

326
00:16:32,763 --> 00:16:34,696
<i>the robot and the duckling</i>

327
00:16:34,729 --> 00:16:36,729
<i>bonded together</i>
<i>at the molecular level</i>

328
00:16:36,763 --> 00:16:39,396
<i>creating that creepy ghost.</i>

329
00:16:39,429 --> 00:16:41,696
KARLA: <i>The robot was</i>
<i>an old road maintenance bot</i>

330
00:16:41,729 --> 00:16:43,829
<i>so it can synchronize</i>
<i>with the frequency</i>

331
00:16:43,863 --> 00:16:46,663
<i>of the holo-projectors in</i>
the tunnels in order to appear.

332
00:16:46,696 --> 00:16:49,829
Now, if you'll excuse us, we
have toxic waste to transport.

333
00:16:49,863 --> 00:16:52,063
But the ghost said
it would be dangerous

334
00:16:52,096 --> 00:16:55,496
to transport any more trash
into hyperspace, so don't!

335
00:16:55,529 --> 00:16:56,729
We don't work
for the ghost.

336
00:16:56,763 --> 00:16:59,029
The people we work for
pay us a lot of money

337
00:16:59,063 --> 00:17:00,729
to dispose
of this toxic stuff.

338
00:17:00,763 --> 00:17:02,863
Besides, old junk
has to be thrown away

339
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:04,663
to make room for new junk.

340
00:17:04,696 --> 00:17:08,496
You can just think of us
as responsible citizens

341
00:17:08,529 --> 00:17:10,463
doing out part to protect
the environment.

342
00:17:10,496 --> 00:17:11,496
[LAUGHING]

343
00:17:11,529 --> 00:17:13,096
Crazy ladies!

344
00:17:13,129 --> 00:17:14,763
I'll put a stop to you

345
00:17:14,796 --> 00:17:17,496
if I have to pull that thing
apart with my bare hands!

346
00:17:17,529 --> 00:17:18,596
Be careful!

347
00:17:20,996 --> 00:17:23,963
[SCREAMING]

348
00:17:23,996 --> 00:17:25,529
That does it!

349
00:17:25,563 --> 00:17:27,796
Nobody messes with my friend!

350
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:30,896
Nagha, show the girl
you want to be her friend too.

351
00:17:32,096 --> 00:17:33,896
[GROANING]

352
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:36,563
[SCREAMING]

353
00:17:36,596 --> 00:17:38,729
If you like the ghost so much,

354
00:17:38,763 --> 00:17:40,963
maybe you'll enjoy living
with him in hyperspace.

355
00:17:40,996 --> 00:17:42,663
[REPO GIRLS LAUGHING]

356
00:17:42,696 --> 00:17:43,929
Enough!

357
00:17:43,963 --> 00:17:46,163
This is no place
for you. Run!

358
00:17:46,196 --> 00:17:48,829
Astro wouldn't run
and neither will I

359
00:17:48,863 --> 00:17:50,463
because I am Astro's sister.

360
00:17:50,496 --> 00:17:52,529
Don't argue with me, Zoran!

361
00:17:55,963 --> 00:17:58,096
Astro, help!

362
00:18:00,096 --> 00:18:02,096
That voice, it's Zoran!

363
00:18:02,129 --> 00:18:04,663
Time to go. Bye-bye.

364
00:18:06,496 --> 00:18:08,629
Zoran, don't look, kiddo.

365
00:18:08,663 --> 00:18:09,863
ASTRO:
Hold it!

366
00:18:09,896 --> 00:18:11,529
ALL:
Huh?

367
00:18:15,896 --> 00:18:19,629
Go, bro! Go, bro! Go, bro!
At last, the star of the show.

368
00:18:19,663 --> 00:18:21,363
Pick on this!

369
00:18:29,796 --> 00:18:32,429
Now I just connect
this to this and--

370
00:18:32,463 --> 00:18:34,063
Hold it, Astro.

371
00:18:34,096 --> 00:18:35,796
You aren't reversing
the projector, are you?

372
00:18:35,829 --> 00:18:37,563
[SCREAMING]

373
00:18:42,863 --> 00:18:44,496
[ALL GASPING]

374
00:18:46,596 --> 00:18:48,696
[ALL SCREAMING]

375
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:53,696
Hey, my duck! Hah!
Be careful!

376
00:18:56,196 --> 00:18:57,763
KISAGARI: Hey,
come back here!

377
00:18:57,796 --> 00:18:59,363
Stop!

378
00:19:01,029 --> 00:19:02,929
Gotcha!

379
00:19:02,963 --> 00:19:04,963
[ALL SCREAMING]

380
00:19:06,929 --> 00:19:10,029
So what are the odds
our probation officer

381
00:19:10,063 --> 00:19:11,963
will overlook
this little slip-up?

382
00:19:11,996 --> 00:19:13,829
[HEADS LAUGHING]

383
00:19:16,063 --> 00:19:18,863
Astro! I wasn't scared.

384
00:19:18,896 --> 00:19:20,929
I know you weren't, sis.

385
00:19:20,963 --> 00:19:22,596
VOICE: Zoran.
Huh?

386
00:19:22,629 --> 00:19:25,996
Thank you for listening
to our message.

387
00:19:26,029 --> 00:19:27,963
Quack, quack,
quack.

388
00:19:27,996 --> 00:19:30,929
Oh, you don't have to thank me,
little friend.

389
00:19:30,963 --> 00:19:32,996
I'd say the whole world
owes you thanks.

390
00:19:33,029 --> 00:19:34,429
Quack.

391
00:19:34,463 --> 00:19:36,929
Oh, you agree with me,
do you?

392
00:19:36,963 --> 00:19:38,896
ZORAN: You can
understand him, mister?

393
00:19:38,929 --> 00:19:42,729
KISAGARI: Sure. After cat, duck
is like a second language to me.

394
00:19:42,763 --> 00:19:44,563
[ALL LAUGHING]

395
00:19:50,663 --> 00:19:52,863
In light of what happened,
I spoke to Zoran

396
00:19:52,896 --> 00:19:54,863
and I offered
to upgrade her.

397
00:19:54,896 --> 00:19:56,929
Yeah? What did
she say to that?

398
00:19:56,963 --> 00:19:59,163
She said,
"No, thank you."

399
00:19:59,196 --> 00:20:01,463
That even without
fire-breath,

400
00:20:01,496 --> 00:20:04,529
she knows she's pretty special
just the way she is.

401
00:20:07,796 --> 00:20:11,596
So I ended up solving
the whole case all by myself.

402
00:20:11,629 --> 00:20:13,496
Guess who's
top robot now.

403
00:20:13,529 --> 00:20:15,429
Me.

404
00:20:15,463 --> 00:20:17,996
You know, talking to animals
is a pretty cool power.

405
00:20:18,029 --> 00:20:19,796
Maybe I need
an upgrade.

406
00:20:19,829 --> 00:20:20,996
Now, don't you start.

407
00:20:23,029 --> 00:20:25,626
[KISAGARI SNEEZES]

408
00:20:25,659 --> 00:20:29,992
That brother and sister are a
couple of good kids, er, robots.

409
00:20:30,026 --> 00:20:32,559
Meow! Meow!

410
00:20:32,592 --> 00:20:35,859
[YELLING]

411
00:20:37,659 --> 00:20:39,892
[♪]

